Date: Tue, 20 Mar 2018 16:59:34 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 555/909] arm64: dts: r8a7795-salvator-xs: Add R-Car H3 ES3.0
 (2 x 2 GiB) support

commit 9fdbc703d4233ad2d5cf105aef7f8913a54139b2 from
git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/horms/renesas-bsp.git

This patch adds initial support for the Renesas Salvator-X 2nd version
development board equipped with an R-Car H3 ES3.0 SiP of 4GiB (2 x 2 GiB)
memory model.

The memory map is as follows:
    Bank0: 2GiB RAM : 0x000048000000 -> 0x000bfffffff
    Bank1: 2GiB RAM : 0x000500000000 -> 0x0057fffffff

Signed-off-by: Takeshi Kihara <takeshi.kihara.df@renesas.com>
[tho.vu.wh: fix dma-ranges property of pcie nodes due to memory map change]
Signed-off-by: Tho Vu <tho.vu.wh@rvc.renesas.com>
Signed-off-by: Takeshi Kihara <takeshi.kihara.df@renesas.com>
Signed-off-by: Meng Li <Meng.Li@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/Makefile          |  1 +
 .../dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-xs-2x2g.dts  | 40 +++++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 41 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-xs-2x2g.dts

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/Makefile b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/Makefile
